@peng-yongsheng These is a case which we must pay attention for. If add this flag, if a already stable system updates and reboots only. the agent definitely lost all caches(peer/operationName dictionary). So agent upstreams segments with isCompleteCompress = false.

By that, collector save the segments and try to process in async ways, with more disk and CPU lost, and more latency. Actually, the peer/operationName caches work fine if you try to compress those segments.

This is not an **infrequent** scenario. Every time, application reboots, this happens. So you must be careful to deal with it.

